The European Community (EC) willretaliate against U.S. textile exports if Congress passes tradelegislation damaging European interests, an EC official warnedtoday.    Roy Denman, head of the EC delegation here, issued thewarning in a letter to Senator Lloyd Bentsen, chairman of theFinance Committee. A copy was provided to Reuters.    The bill, backed by the textile industry and senators fromtextile-producing states, would impose global quotas on textileimports and for the first time include Europe.    Denman said he was concerned about provisions in the billthat would limit, if not eliminate, the president's discretionin retaliating against nations that keep their home marketsclosed to foreign goods. Reuter&#3;